The paper discusses a new algorithm for off-policy learning with exploration-exploitation trade-off, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. The algorithm is of the gradient type and can be used with function approximators such as neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
